last_episode_to_air.name: Surgeons, Bachelors and Butchers
last_episode_to_air.overview: The doctors in Sweden defend their findings to the Karolinska board, and their report leaks to the press. Benita’s colleague publishes the story of Paolo’s deception and misconduct. Swedish authorities make a decision about Macchiarini’s case.

name: Dr. Death
overview: An anthology series, with each season following a new medical true crime story.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: The terrifying true story of Dr. Christopher Duntsch, a flourishing Dallas neurosurgeon whose patients suddenly begin becoming permanently maimed or dead. As victims piled up, two fellow physicians set out to stop him.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Season 2 follows “Miracle Man” Paolo Macchiarini, a charming surgeon renowned for his innovative operations. When investigative journalist Benita Alexander approaches him for a story, the line between personal and professional begins to blur, changing her life forever. As she learns how far Paolo will go to protect his secrets, a group of doctors halfway across the world make shocking discoveries of their own that call everything about Paolo into question.

episodes.name: Diplos
episodes.overview: Two doctors investigate the maiming and death of patients at the hands of a Dallas neurosurgeon.

episodes.name: Ain't No Bum
episodes.overview: Henderson and Kirby try to strip Duntsch of his medical license; Duntsch joins the football team.

episodes.name: Dock Ellis
episodes.overview: Duntsch meets his mentor; Henderson and Kirby explore the medical system.

episodes.name: An Occurrence at Randall Kirby's Sink
episodes.overview: Henderson and Kirby crash a function in Duntsch's honor; Duntsch sets up his practice in Texas.

episodes.name: The $?!& in the Bed
episodes.overview: Duntsch begins operating in Dallas; Henderson and Kirby gain an ally in stopping Duntsch.

episodes.name: Occam's Razor
episodes.overview: Duntsch attempts to fix a disastrous surgery; Shughart builds her case against Duntsch.

episodes.name: Feet of Clay
episodes.overview: Duntsch tries to mount a defense; Henderson, Kirby and Shughart seek answers to lingering questions.

episodes.name: Hardwood Floors
episodes.overview: Duntsch's victims confront him as Henderson, Kirby and Shughart set out to put him behind bars.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: The terrifying true story of Dr. Christopher Duntsch, a flourishing Dallas neurosurgeon whose patients suddenly begin becoming permanently maimed or dead. As victims piled up, two fellow physicians set out to stop him.

episodes.name: Like Magic
episodes.overview: In 2012, Dr. Macchiarini performs a breakthrough thoracic surgery, but some colleagues in Sweden question his science. In the present, Macchiarini operates on Hannah and becomes romantically involved with Benita, a news producer covering the surgery.

episodes.name: Worth the Risk
episodes.overview: In 2012, Macchiarini’s research gets published after his patient in Sweden is asymptomatic two months post-surgery. In the present, Hannah suffers complications. Paolo and Benita grow closer. Paolo seeks new patients to expand his practice.

episodes.name: The Horizon
episodes.overview: In 2012 Stockholm, another Dr. Macchiarini surgery ends tragically. In the present, Benita meets Paolo’s parents and decides to investigate his background before moving with him to Barcelona.

episodes.name: Tarantela Telaraña
episodes.overview: In the past, doctors in Sweden and Belgium suspect that Dr. Macchiarini is not running animal trials and is instead experimenting on people. Benita realizes Paolo’s promises are lies and uncovers dark secrets from his past.

Yesim, a young Turkish woman, travels to Sweden for a consultation and ends up on Dr. Macchiarini’s operating table. Dr. Gamelli fights to keep Yesim alive and forcefully raises concerns about Macchiarini’s procedure.

episodes.name: The Fog
episodes.overview: In Russia, Macchiarini is set to perform elective surgery on the wife of an oligarch, but Dr. Lasbrey convinces her to postpone it. Benita realizes Paolo’s lies go deeper than she thought. Ana returns to Sweden and confirms her suspicions.

episodes.name: Compassionate Uses
episodes.overview: Doctors Gamelli, Svensson and Lasbrey blow the whistle on Macchiarini but face the consequences. In Russia, Paolo convinces Yulia to go through with the surgery. Benita struggles to tell her story.

episodes.name: Surgeons, Bachelors and Butchers
episodes.overview: The doctors in Sweden defend their findings to the Karolinska board, and their report leaks to the press. Benita’s colleague publishes the story of Paolo’s deception and misconduct. Swedish authorities make a decision about Macchiarini’s case.
